# Next.js auto-regenerates next-env.d.ts on every build (including a
# build-output `<reference path>` line that points into .next/). Committing it
# means the reference is dangling on a clean clone before any build has run.
# Per Next.js convention, this file is safe to gitignore.
**/next-env.d.ts
.turbo/
*.log
.DS_Store
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
coverage/
*.tsbuildinfo
.idea/
.vscode/
*.Zone.Identifier
.vercel
